Ask HN: Good RSS Feeds for US News?
text:
I am experimenting with a smart RSS reader that filters my feeds. One of my favorite sources is The Guardian, which is strong on world news and particularly the UK and Australia.

Although watching the decline and fall of the remnants of the British empire is quite entertaining and The Guardian has some US news I feel I am not getting enough US news in my mix.

There are numerous things I like about The Guardian such as: (i) their outlook, (ii) quality of reporting, (iii) volume of output, (iv) substantial text (but not too much) in the feed, and (v) no paywall.

Are there good RSS feeds for US news that share some of these attributes?

Ask HN: Jailbreaking iPhone getting ever harder. Should EU sue Apple?
text:
I think when you buy a device, you own it and should be able to do whatever you want with it (unless it's harming others). I've been a long time iPhone/iPad user and used to jailbreak my iDevices, but recent versions of Apple chips make it almost impossible to jailbreak the device. I understand the risks, but who is Apple to decide what I can and cannot do with my device after I purchase it at their premium prices no less?

I think the EU has focused on the wrong problems, namely, USB C. Whereas a truly open device must in fact provide a jailbreak switch deep in the settings app where users can freely toggle should they want less restricted access.
